  createNode(nodes, secondBrainGuideId, rootId, "Second Brain", "Your Second Brain is a special, always-present outline where you accumulate everything you want to remember — notes, research, ideas, articles, images, anything. It's your personal knowledge base, searchable by natural language via AI.\n\nThe Second Brain outline is created automatically when you first launch the app. It appears at the top of your outline list with a 🧠 icon and cannot be deleted or renamed.\n\nAll existing features work on it: import from any source, merge outlines into it, export in any format, expand content with AI. The difference is it's always there, always pinned, and has its own dedicated search mode.", []);

  createNode(nodes, sbSaveId, secondBrainGuideId, "Saving to Second Brain", "Save any node (and its entire suboutline) to your Second Brain:\n\n**From the context menu:**\n1. Right-click any node in any outline\n2. Select '🧠 Save to Second Brain'\n3. The node and all its children are copied into your Second Brain\n\n**From the toolbar:**\n1. Select a node\n2. Click the 🧠 brain icon in the toolbar\n3. Select 'Save Selection to Second Brain'\n\n**Keyboard shortcut:** ⌘⇧B (Cmd+Shift+B)\n\nThe original node stays in place — a copy is added to the Second Brain.");

  createNode(nodes, sbSearchId, secondBrainGuideId, "Asking Your Second Brain", "Query your Second Brain with natural language:\n\n**From the toolbar:**\n1. Click the 🧠 brain icon\n2. Select 'Ask Second Brain'\n3. Ask Your Outlines opens in Second Brain mode (green button)\n4. Ask any question — the AI searches only your Second Brain content\n\n**Keyboard shortcut:** ⌘⇧S (Cmd+Shift+S)\n\nYou can also open Ask Your Outlines from the Smart Tools menu and switch to the 🧠 Second Brain tab manually.\n\n**Example questions:**\n- 'What do I know about machine learning?'\n- 'Summarize my notes on the competitor analysis'\n- 'Find everything related to quarterly goals'");

  createNode(nodes, sbMenuId, secondBrainGuideId, "Second Brain Toolbar Menu", "The 🧠 brain icon in the toolbar gives you quick access to all Second Brain actions:\n\n- **Open Second Brain** — switches to the Second Brain outline (no shortcut: ⌘B is reserved for the sidebar)\n- **Quick Capture** (⌘⇧I) — drop a quick thought into your Inbox from anywhere\n- **Save Selection to Second Brain** (⌘⇧B) — copies selected node and suboutline\n- **Search Second Brain** (magnifying-glass icon) — FREE, instant, local keyword search that filters your saved entries by title and content. No AI, no internet, no cost.\n- **Ask Second Brain** (chat-bubble icon, ⌘⇧S) — AI answer about your saved content. Uses an AI generation.\n- **View Dashboard** — overview of recent saves, revisit pile, and top tags\n- **Import to Second Brain** — switches to Second Brain and opens Research & Import\n\n**Search vs. Ask — know the difference:** *Search* just finds the entries whose words match what you type (like Ctrl-F over your saves) and costs nothing. *Ask* sends your question to the AI, which reads across your saves and writes an answer — that's the paid one.");

  createNode(nodes, sbLocalSearchId, secondBrainGuideId, "Search Second Brain (free & instant)", "A free, instant, local keyword search over everything you've saved — no AI, no internet, no cost.\n\n**Access:** 🧠 Brain menu > Search Second Brain (the magnifying-glass item). The Dashboard opens with the search box already focused.\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Start typing in the search box at the top of the Dashboard\n2. Your saved entries filter live as you type — matching on both the title and the full content of each entry\n3. Matching is case-insensitive and ignores extra spaces\n4. Click any result to jump straight to that entry\n\nThe search box is always there at the top of the Dashboard, so you can filter your saves any time you open it.\n\n**Search vs. Ask:** Search is a plain word-match filter (free, instant, works offline). *Ask Second Brain* is different — it sends your question to the AI to get a written answer, and it uses one of your AI generations.");

  createNode(nodes, sbQuickCaptureId, secondBrainGuideId, "Quick Capture", "Drop any thought into your Second Brain from anywhere in the app — no need to navigate to an outline first.\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Press ⌘⇧I (Cmd+Shift+I) — a floating dialog appears\n2. Type or paste any text (a thought, a quote, a link, a reminder)\n3. Hit Enter or click \"Save to Inbox\"\n4. Your entry lands in a 📥 Inbox section at the top of your Second Brain\n\n**No keyboard? No problem.** Click the 🧠 brain icon in the toolbar and choose Quick Capture. The same dialog opens — works on iPad/iPhone where ⌘⇧I isn't available.\n\nThe Inbox is created automatically the first time you use Quick Capture. The first 60 characters become the node name; anything longer goes into the content pane.\n\n**Smart auto-tagging:** Right after saving, the AI suggests 1-3 short topical tags and applies them automatically. A toast tells you which tags were added.\n\nPerfect for friction-free capture during reading, meetings, or any moment when an idea hits.");

  createNode(nodes, sbDashboardId, secondBrainGuideId, "Second Brain Dashboard", "Get a bird's-eye view of your Second Brain — what you've saved, what to revisit, and what topics dominate.\n\n**Access:** 🧠 Brain menu > View Dashboard\n\n**What it shows:**\n- **Search box (top)** — a FREE, instant, local keyword search. Type to filter your saved entries by title and content; no AI and no cost. See \"Search Second Brain (free & instant)\".\n- **Total entries** — how much you've accumulated overall\n- **Recent saves (last 7 days)** — what you've added this week\n- **Revisit pile** — older entries the AI nudges you to revisit so they don't get buried\n- **Top tags** — your most common topics, useful for spotting themes\n\nClick any entry in the dashboard to jump straight to that node in your Second Brain.");

  createNode(nodes, sbAutoTagId, secondBrainGuideId, "Smart Auto-Tagging", "Every time you save something to your Second Brain — via Quick Capture, Save Selection, or Import — the AI automatically suggests 1-3 short topical tags and applies them to the new node.\n\n**Why tags matter:**\n- Tags are stored as node metadata and shown in the Dashboard's \"Top tags\" section\n- Helps the AI find related material when you search\n- Makes the Revisit pile more meaningful — you can see at a glance what each item is about\n\n**Adjusting tags:** Tags are non-blocking — your save always succeeds first, then tags arrive a moment later. You can edit them anytime via the existing tag UI on the node.\n\nTags are short, lowercase, hyphenated (e.g. `machine-learning`, `quarterly-goals`).");

