  createNode(nodes, richTextId, mediaId, "Rich Text Formatting", "The content editor supports full rich text formatting:\n\n**Text Styling:**\n- Bold: Cmd+B (Ctrl+B on Windows)\n- Italic: Cmd+I (Ctrl+I on Windows)\n- Strikethrough\n\n**Headings:**\n- H1, H2, H3 heading levels\n\n**Lists:**\n- Ordered (numbered) lists\n- Unordered (bullet) lists\n- Checklist (task) lists with checkboxes\n\n**Code:**\n- Code blocks with syntax formatting\n\n**Undo/Redo (unified across everything you do):**\n- Undo: Cmd+Z (Ctrl+Z)\n- Redo: Cmd+Shift+Z (Ctrl+Shift+Z)\n- One shortcut undoes whatever you just did — text edits inside a node, adding or deleting items, moving items around, AI transforms (Reformat, Translate, Transform Outline, Refresh from Web), pastes, and imports. Undo depth has no hard cap.\n- After a big change (an AI transform, an import, a multi-item delete) Cmd+Z shows a persistent toast like \"Undid: Translate Outline\" so you can see exactly what reverted. The toast stays on screen until you click the X to dismiss it.\n\nAll formatting is preserved when you switch between nodes or close the app.\n\n**Touch-Accessible Toolbar (works on iPhone, iPad, and desktop):**\n- The content pane toolbar now includes **Undo** and **Redo** buttons at the left end, plus **Bullet List**, **Numbered List**, and **Checklist** buttons. These give you one-tap access to the most common editor actions without needing a keyboard or a right-click context menu.\n- **Floating formatting toolbar** — select any text in the editor and a small floating menu appears above the selection with Bold, Italic, Strikethrough, Inline Code, and Heading 1/2/3 buttons. Active formatting is highlighted so you can see what's already applied. This works on both desktop and touch devices.\n\n**Links:**\nPaste URLs from your clipboard and they automatically become clickable links. Links from rich HTML (e.g. copied from ChatGPT or web pages) are also preserved. Links open in a new tab when clicked.");

  createNode(nodes, googleDocsId, mediaId, "Google Docs Embedding", "Embed Google Docs directly in your content:\n\n1. Click the + (Insert) menu in the content toolbar\n2. Paste a Google Docs URL\n3. The document renders as an inline preview\n\nThe embedded doc displays within your content pane. The document must be publicly shared or shared with you.");

  createNode(nodes, googleSheetsId, mediaId, "Google Sheets Embedding", "Embed Google Sheets directly in your content:\n\n1. Click the + (Insert) menu in the content toolbar\n2. Paste a Google Sheets URL\n3. The spreadsheet renders as an inline preview\n\nUseful for referencing live data, shared budgets, or tracking sheets within your outline.");

